        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>246 W 52.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                My dear sir<lb/></p>
            <p>If &#36;10 would procure<lb/> the Revd. Is. and other Bible comments of Luzzato<lb/> as you state you think&#44; I shall be very glad if<lb/> you will order them for me&#44; that is&#44; if not<lb/> troubling you.  The circular on this will<lb/> interest you.  With regards<lb/></p>
            <p>Yrs try<lb/>
                H Mendes.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Nineteenth Street Synagogue&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>KISLEV&#44; 5641&#44;<lb/>
                NOVEMBER&#44; 1880.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>DEAR SIR&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have much pleasure in informing you&#44; that the Ladies&#39; Classes<lb/> attached to our Congregation&#44; will commence the new session on Wednesday&#44;<lb/> the 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> inst.<lb/></p>
            <p>The education of children by home influence&#44;&#45;&#45;the most potent educator&#44;&#45;&#45;de&#45;<lb/>pends in a very great measure upon the Ladies.  That they should be qualified<lb/> to exert this influence is a most solemn duty&#59; that they are willing to receive<lb/> the necessary instruction is evidenced by the many who have attended&#44; by the<lb/> many who have already signified their intention of joining.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have therefore&#44; to ask your kind offices in bringing these classes to the no&#45;<lb/>tice of all&#44; and to assure them that the difficulties popularly supposed to envelop<lb/> the sacred language are removed by the method employed&#44; which renders each<lb/> lesson interesting and quickly deprives the study of its supposed dryness.<lb/></p>
            <p>A primary class will be this year instituted.  A course of Lectures upon<lb/> LITERATURE and HISTORY&#44; will be inaugurated if practicable.<lb/></p>
            <p>In addition to the Ladies&#39; Classes&#44; others will be established for<lb/></p>
            <p>YOUNG MEN OF THE CONGREGATION.<lb/></p>
            <p>There are&#44; I am confident&#44; young men in our Congregation who are far too<lb/> sensible and earnest to be content to be Hebrews&#44; and know little or nothing<lb/> of the language&#44; past history and future hopes of our nation.<lb/></p>
            <p>The absurdity of being Jews and knowing nothing of Jewish law or lore&#44; is so<lb/> evident to any thinking man&#44; that he will spare not effort to repair his deficien&#45;<lb/>cies&#59; nor will he think it too great a sacrifice or too unmanly&#44; to devote at<lb/> least one hour a week to the study of subjects which transform the Jew by<lb/> birth&#44; into the Jew by conviction and knowledge.<lb/></p>
            <p>A young&#45;men&#39;s class maintained through last winter&#44; is sufficient evidence<lb/> that it can be successful.  Those even who know not the letters&#44; will be able to<lb/> read and translate passages before the session is over.<lb/></p>
            <p>I will be happy to attend a class of THREE OR MORE AT ANY RESIDENCE any<lb/> convenient evening.<lb/>
                Additional effort will this year be made on behalf of the<lb/></p>
            <p>CHILDREN OF MEMBERS.<lb/></p>
            <p>If we desire the children of the Congregation to become Hebrews worthy of<lb/> the name&#44; that is&#44; with a proper knowledge of the language and sacred tradition<lb/> which together distinguish our nation&#44; we must find means to impart such<lb/> knowledge outside of the public schools.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>The Sunday School&#44; admirable as is its influence in this direction&#44; is not suf&#45;<lb/>ficient.  To supplement its usefulness by week&#45;day classes is the only method<lb/> to solve the problem.<lb/></p>
            <p>There will therefore be a class for children of members of our Congregation&#44;<lb/> every Tuesday afternoon&#44; at Synagogue&#44; from 3&#58;30 to 4&#58;30 P.M.<lb/></p>
            <p>By establishing the above classes I trust to gradually diffuse Hebrew educa&#45;<lb/>tion throughout the whole Congregation&#44; being firmly convinced that the hope<lb/> of Judaism lies in the Jewish education of those whose faith it is&#44; and that our<lb/> own community can only perform its duty in preserving historic Judaism&#44; by re&#45;<lb/>newed activity and energy in the educational department.<lb/></p>
            <p><emph rend="italics">I am&#44; sir</emph><lb/>
                <emph rend="italics">Yours very truly&#44;</emph><lb/>
                H. P. MENDES&#44;<lb/>
                <emph rend="italics">Minister&#44; K. K. S. I.</emph><lb/></p>
                
            <p>LIST OF CLASSES.<lb/>
                LADIES&#39; CLASSES.<lb/>
                WEDNESDAYS AT THE 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> STREET SYNAGOGUE.<lb/></p>
            <p>CLASS A. &#40;2 P.M.&#45;&#45;3 P. M.&#41; Translation of Psalms&#44; passages of Historical and Prophetic Books&#59; Heb. Grammar.<lb/></p>
            <p>CLASS B. &#40;3 P.M.&#45;&#45;4 P.M.&#41; Translation of passages of Pentateuch&#44; Prayers&#44; easy Hebrew Grammar.<lb/></p>
            <p>CLASS C. &#40;4 P.M.&#45;&#45;5 P.M.&#41; Primary Class. Reading and first principles of Hebrew Grammar.<lb/></p>
            <p>YOUNG MEN&#39;S CLASSES. &#40;EVENING.&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>Gentlemen willing to devote an hour a week&#44; or more&#44; to Hebrew&#44; are requested to communicate with me at<lb/> No. 244 West 52d Street.<lb/></p>
            <p>POST GRADUATE CLASS &#40;EVENING.&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>Meets now.  Originally designed for certificated graduates of the Sunday School&#44; it is open to all desirous of<lb/> joining.<lb/></p>
            <p>CLASSES FOR CHILDREN OF MEMBERS.<lb/></p>
            <p>One is already established&#59; another will meet at Synagogue&#44; Tuesdays&#44; 3&#58;30&#8212;4&#58;30 P.M.<lb/></p>
            <p>GENERAL WEEK&#45;DAY CLASSES.<lb/></p>
            <p>Graded Classes&#44; Thursdays&#44; at Synagogue&#44; 3&#58;30 P.M.  Address at 4&#58;15 P.M.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>&#40;<emph rend="italics">Further Particulars of all the above Classes upon application.</emph>&#41;<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                546 North 5th<lb/>
                Phila.<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
